results.occurrenceRemarks: A last minute opportunity to do the "albatross encounter" trip at Kaikoura resulted in a great range of species for a winter trip. It was a rough day so we had to stay within the shelter of the peninsula but nevertheless a good range of pelagic species came to the boat. We saw 6 white-capped mollymawk. I note that other authorities list this species as Thalassarche steadi

Great Otway National Park (Sheoak Falls Track), Beginning at the car park off Great Ocean Rd, this track follows the coast before veering inland running adjacent to Sheoak Creek through Sheoak dominated forest. The track eventually reaches Sheoak Picnic Ground. Along the creek is a good area to find Rufous Bristlebird.

Adventure Bay, Adventure Bay on southeast Bruny Island incorporates a series of beaches and adjacent  stands of fairly open Eucalypt forest . After passing Cemetery Bluff the first beach is known colloquially as "cemetery" beach. After Two Tree Point comes Barkers beach which is separated from Adventure Bay beach by a headland. After the main beach, which is several kilometres in length, there is a rocky shore for a kilometre or so before East Cove beach, which leads into Fluted Cape national park. Coolangatta and Lockleys roads lead inland into wet Eucalypt and rainforest.
